  read.delim(
    '${asv_table_file}', 
    header=T, 
    sep='\t',
    stringsAsFactors=F
    )

  read.delim(
    '${taxonomy_table_file}',

    sep='\t',
    stringsAsFactors=F

  mutate_all(as.character())

{
  sample_data = 
    sample_data %>%
    filter(IGA=='AllBac')

  sample_names = sample_data$SampleName
  
  asv_table = 
    asv_table %>%
    select('ASVs', ends_with('AllBac'))

```r
ps = phyloseq(
  otu_table(asv_table %>%
              remove_rownames() %>%
              column_to_rownames('ASVs') %>%
              as.matrix(),
    taxa_are_rows=T
  ),
  tax_table(taxonomy_table %>%
              remove_rownames() %>%
              column_to_rownames('ASVs') %>%
              as.matrix()
  ),
  sample_data(sample_data %>%
                remove_rownames() %>%
                column_to_rownames('SampleName')
              ),
  phy_tree(fit$tree)
)

```r
for (var in variables)
{
  var_data = observational_variables[[var]]
  print(var_data)
  
  remove_idx = 
    sample_data %>%
    mutate(
      remove_idx = (!!as.name(var) %in% c(var_data$case, var_data$control))
      ) %>%
    pull(remove_idx)
  
  this_ps = prune_samples(remove_idx, ps)
  
  ps_ord = ordinate(this_ps, 'PCoA', 'UNIFRAC', weighted=T)
  
  for (axes in axes_sets)
  {
    print(axes)
    
    plotUnifracOrd(
      this_ps, 
      ps_ord, 
      ord_type = 'PCoA',
      dist_type='UNIFRAC',
      weighted=T, 
      axes=axes,
      var_data = observational_variables[[var]],
      color=var,
      plot_type='samples'
    ) %>% print()
  }
  
}

0.2.2.3 2D

for (var in variables)
{
  var_data = observational_variables[[var]]
  print(var_data)
  
  remove_idx = 
    sample_data %>%
    filter(Age < 90) %>%
    mutate(
      remove_idx = (!!as.name(var) %in% c(var_data$case, var_data$control))
      ) %>%
    pull(remove_idx)
  
  this_ps = prune_samples(remove_idx, ps_age_lt_90)
  
  ps_ord = ordinate(this_ps, 'PCoA', 'UNIFRAC', weighted=F)
  
  for (axes in axes_sets)
  {
    print(axes)
    
    plotUnifracOrd(
      this_ps, 
      ps_ord, 
      ord_type = 'PCoA',
      dist_type='UNIFRAC',
      weighted=F, 
      axes=axes,
      var_data = observational_variables[[var]],
      color=var,
      plot_type='samples'
    ) %>% print()
  }
  
}
